<recipe>
<title>
Caramelized Onions
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
3 sweet onions , peeled and thinly sliced
1 ½ T . butter
1 ½ T . olive oil
1 tsp . granulated sugar
Salt
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in olive oil.
Add onions to skillet and toss to coat in butter and olive oil.
Let the onions cook slowly over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Once the onions to begun to turn golden brown, add the sugar and a sprinkle of salt. Stir to combine.
Keep cooking the onions over low heat until they’re an amber brown.
</instructions>
</recipe>
